one of your [foreign
language] companions.

00:15:31.510 --> 00:15:35.010
And my illuminations
play on the idea

00:15:35.010 --> 00:15:40.130
of the passionate love it expresses
between god and the human soul.

00:15:40.130 --> 00:15:44.760 position:56%
Obzekrid [phonetic] describes god as
the soul's beloved, soul's father,

00:15:44.760 --> 00:15:48.320
soul's light, soul's
protector, soul's glory.

00:15:48.320 --> 00:15:52.190
Always returning to the intimate
language of romantic love

00:15:52.190 --> 00:15:55.780
to express the depth of
human emotion to god.

00:15:55.780 --> 00:15:59.540
Whether father, healing
light, or protective king,

00:15:59.540 --> 00:16:03.110
god is the intimate
eternal beloved of the soul.

00:16:03.110 --> 00:16:07.290
The microcopy that you see, the
lines of tiny writing that you see,

00:16:07.290 --> 00:16:10.620
winding through the paintings,
includes the full text

00:16:10.620 --> 00:16:12.860
of the biblical Song of Songs.

00:16:12.860 --> 00:16:18.030
The love poetry that inspired the
themes of divine and erotic love

00:16:18.030 --> 00:16:21.590
and union that pervade
Jewish mysticism.

00:16:21.590 --> 00:16:25.700
Other imagery, the intense
love of a father for his baby.

00:16:25.700 --> 00:16:30.210
A gazelle, this gazelle nested
securely in the forest floor,

00:16:30.210 --> 00:16:33.070
captures other qualities
of the human --

00:16:33.070 --> 00:16:37.330
of the warm human love for the
divine that the poet expresses.

00:16:37.330 --> 00:16:43.180 position:56%
And these scenes reflect also the
unity of the whole biological world,

00:16:43.180 --> 00:16:45.290
the whole material world.

00:16:45.290 --> 00:16:48.430
Our history also unites us.

00:16:48.430 --> 00:16:50.080
The columns of palmets [phonetic]

00:16:50.080 --> 00:16:53.550
that you see flanking
the text are adapted

00:16:53.550 --> 00:16:58.820
from a little ivory furniture
plaque now in the Israel museum

00:16:58.820 --> 00:17:02.850
