which is exactly contemporary

00:17:02.850 --> 00:17:05.180
with the building of
Solomon's temple and palace.

00:17:05.180 --> 00:17:08.680
In the biblical books
of Kings and Chronicles,

00:17:08.680 --> 00:17:11.910 position:56%
palmets [phonetic] patterns are
described for those great buildings.

00:17:11.910 --> 00:17:15.970
And there's perfectly solid art
historical reason to suspect

00:17:15.970 --> 00:17:18.770
that this pattern is the
very one that was used

00:17:18.770 --> 00:17:21.350 position:56%
in decorating those great buildings.

00:17:21.350 --> 00:17:24.300
And so I use these palmets
[phonetic] often in my work,

00:17:24.300 --> 00:17:28.730
to allude to the importance of the
temple as god's dwelling on earth

00:17:28.730 --> 00:17:34.310 position:56%
and the historical unity of Jewish
community across time and geography.

00:17:34.310 --> 00:17:37.820 position:56%
There's much more detailed symbolism
in each of these paintings,

00:17:37.820 --> 00:17:40.250
but I'll let you read
about that in the book.

00:17:40.250 --> 00:17:45.400 position:56%
But, again, the infant and the force
imagery remind us of the importance

00:17:45.400 --> 00:17:48.970
of living our spiritual
life through the wonders

00:17:48.970 --> 00:17:51.750
of the natural world
that we inhabit.

00:17:51.750 --> 00:17:55.590
One of the signal ways in which
Jews sanctify the 25 hours

00:17:55.590 --> 00:17:59.530
of the Sabbath is with the
Kiddush, the blessing over wine

00:17:59.530 --> 00:18:02.390
at the beginning of
the Sabbath meals.

00:18:02.390 --> 00:18:06.830
Now, in the Kabbalistic sources,
wine is a symbol of divine wisdom.

00:18:06.830 --> 00:18:08.550
And the Sabbath is the time

00:18:08.550 --> 00:18:13.370
that wisdom flows most
abundantly into the material realm.

00:18:13.370 --> 00:18:17.250
My interpretations of kiddush
present the mystical idea

00:18:17.250 --> 00:18:22.130
of the wine's translation of divine
wisdom into the material world

00:18:22.130 --> 00:18:25.010
through a mathematical metaphor.

00:18:25.010 --> 00:18:29.290
So here at right, the Hebrew
lumination plays with the image

00:18:29.290 --> 00:18:33.250
of the wine fountains, with
which many Jews share kiddush

00:18:33.250 --> 00:18:35.930
with the family and
friends at our tables.

00:18:35.930 --> 00:18:39.470
These cups though aren't arrayed
on the typical tiered trays

00:18:39.470 --> 00:18:43.190
but pipe wine from the
uppermost to the lower cups.

00:18:43.190 --> 00:18:44.490
And this wine is much more

00:18:44.490 --> 00:18:47.050
than fermented grape
juice, even the best.

00:18:47.050 --> 00:18:51.680
Instead, this wine overflows
from one level to the next,

00:18:51.680 --> 00:18:57.150 position:56%
following the mystical metaphor that
describes how divine wisdom flows

00:18:57.150 --> 00:19:00.510
from the highest, most
hidden aspects of god,

00:19:00.510 --> 00:19:03.630
downward until it reaches
the material world,

00:19:03.630 --> 00:19:06.860
and finally appears to us as water.

00:19:06.860 --> 00:19:11.400
The 10 cups refer, if you haven't
already guessed, to the 10 sefirot,

00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:14.370
or emanations, or qualities of god.

00:19:14.370 --> 00:19:18.040
And they're presented here in
colors associated with each

00:19:18.040 --> 00:19:19.940
of them in the zohar [phonetic].

00:19:19.940 --> 00:19:22.710
But what's this pyramid
arrangement all about?

00:19:22.710 --> 00:19:27.450
Now, just as the kabbalistic system
ascribes the number 10 cosmic

00:19:27.450 --> 00:19:32.400 position:56%
significance -- for instance, the 10
sefirot -- Pythagorean philosophy,

00:19:32.400 --> 00:19:34.650
the beginning of Western
mathematics,

00:19:34.650 --> 00:19:38.180
also regard the number 10 as holy.

00:19:38.180 --> 00:19:40.520
They describe the tech
tractors [phonetic],

00:19:40.520 --> 00:19:44.510
the pyramid symbolizing the unity
of the universe that's formed

00:19:44.510 --> 00:19:49.120
by the flow of geometric
form from a single point.

00:19:49.120 --> 00:19:53.050
The four levels of these cups
Pythagorean pyramid trace the

00:19:53.050 --> 00:19:56.080
development of geometric
form as follows.

00:19:56.080 --> 00:20:00.300
At top, the single cup
represents a single point.

00:20:00.300 --> 00:20:05.240
At the second level, the two cups
represent the two points necessary

00:20:05.240 --> 00:20:07.300
to determine a line.

00:20:07.300 --> 00:20:11.610
At the third level, the three
cups are the three points defining

00:20:11.610 --> 00:20:12.910
a plane.

00:20:12.910 --> 00:20:17.420
And finally, at bottom, the four
cups are the four points necessary

00:20:17.420 --> 00:20:21.820
to determine a tetrahedron, the
simplest three-dimensional form.

00:20:21.820 --> 00:20:26.210
The microcopy surrounding both
these pages is the passage

00:20:26.210 --> 00:20:31.110
from Proverbs 8, in which
wisdom, personified as a woman,

00:20:31.110 --> 00:20:34.640
rejoices in being the
almighty's first companion

00:20:34.640 --> 00:20:36.870
from before creation.

00:20:36.870 --> 00:20:41.560 position:56%
And how she takes pleasure, not only
in being god's closest companion,

00:20:41.560 --> 00:20:45.430
but also a playmate of
humankind, bridging the divide

00:20:45.430 --> 00:20:47.990
between heaven and earth.

00:20:47.990 --> 00:20:50.380
Since time is short,
I'll leave you to find

00:20:50.380 --> 00:20:52.960
out about the English
painting in the book.

00:20:52.960 --> 00:20:56.420
This is all about Luria's
ideas about the sweetness

00:20:56.420 --> 00:20:58.820
of the sheena's presence on earth.

00:20:58.820 --> 00:21:05.040
I love the kabbalistic notion
of how we draw divine wisdom

00:21:05.040 --> 00:21:07.590
into the world on the Sabbath.

00:21:07.590 --> 00:21:11.880
As we saw, blessing wine is an
important means of doing this,

00:21:11.880 --> 00:21:16.200 position:56%
but we begin the process by lighting
Sabbath candles a few minutes

00:21:16.200 --> 00:21:18.240
before sunset.

00:21:18.240 --> 00:21:21.690
My own private prayer, after
blessing the candles, in fact,

00:21:21.690 --> 00:21:26.510
asks for wisdom for guiding my
family and to imbue my work.

00:21:26.510 --> 00:21:29.560
In these paintings of candle
lighting, I fuse the light

00:21:29.560 --> 00:21:33.730
of the candles with the
lights of material creation.

00:21:33.730 --> 00:21:35.920
There's so much going on here.

00:21:35.920 --> 00:21:39.650
Medieval poetry and [foreign
language] historical women's

00:21:39.650 --> 00:21:43.330
meditations, my mother's and
grandmother's candlesticks,

00:21:43.330 --> 00:21:45.190
and all that's explained
in the book.

00:21:45.190 --> 00:21:48.630
But right now, let me just
focus on the sources of light.

00:21:48.630 --> 00:21:52.550
First though, a few words about
the origin and mystical role

00:21:52.550 --> 00:21:54.360
of Sabbath candle lighting.

00:21:54.360 --> 00:21:57.320
The ritual began in the
period of the Mishnah,

00:21:57.320 --> 00:22:01.270
that is in the first couple of
centuries of the Common Era,

00:22:01.270 --> 00:22:05.080
during the period of the first
codification of Jewish law.

00:22:05.080 --> 00:22:08.670
And it was begun simply
to light the Sabbath table

00:22:08.670 --> 00:22:12.320
so that family could relax
and enjoy their festive meal

00:22:12.320 --> 00:22:15.880
and Sabbath rest together
at leisure.

00:22:15.880 --> 00:22:18.880
Mystical sources though
suggests that the light

00:22:18.880 --> 00:22:21.880
from the Sabbath candles adds
to the [foreign language],

00:22:21.880 --> 00:22:26.120
the additional soul that
flowers within the soul

00:22:26.120 --> 00:22:28.490
of every Jew during the Sabbath.

00:22:28.490 --> 00:22:31.320
Now, this [foreign
language], additional soul,

00:22:31.320 --> 00:22:35.800 position:56%
descends from the feminine emanation
of god, the [foreign language],

00:22:35.800 --> 00:22:39.170
the divine emanation
closest in material world.

00:22:39.170 --> 00:22:42.480
It's the woman of the house
who enjoys the privilege

00:22:42.480 --> 00:22:47.180
of lighting the candles, reenacting
the unification of the human

00:22:47.180 --> 00:22:51.820
and divine spheres, of the sphere
of the emanations themselves.

00:22:51.820 --> 00:22:55.840
So let's focus for a moment on
the Hebrew illumination at right.

00:22:55.840 --> 00:23:00.630
Let's start with the
candle flames at the center.

00:23:00.630 --> 00:23:04.380
Their blue and gold motif
represents the [foreign language],

00:23:04.380 --> 00:23:08.520
the divine energy flowing
throughout the universe.

00:23:08.520 --> 00:23:13.230
We view the candles against the
dusk sky lit by the setting sun,

00:23:13.230 --> 00:23:16.590
while the ever-evolving
deep sky wheels far

00:23:16.590 --> 00:23:18.790
above our heads and homes.

00:23:18.790 --> 00:23:22.390
Now, this image is taken from that
same Hubble photograph I showed you

00:23:22.390 --> 00:23:26.950
earlier, showing lights of
origin so distant that it comes

00:23:26.950 --> 00:23:31.390
from the earliest periods
after the Big Bang.

00:23:31.390 --> 00:23:34.400
The geometric painting
surrounding the words

00:23:34.400 --> 00:23:37.320
of the blessing is a
classical Moorish pattern,

00:23:37.320 --> 00:23:41.380 position:56%
that was part of the visual
surroundings of the Sephardic world,

00:23:41.380 --> 00:23:43.540
the world of the Spanish Jews.

00:23:43.540 --> 00:23:47.710
This pattern expresses the
flow of all geometric form

00:23:47.710 --> 00:23:53.170
from a single point, symbolizing
the origin of all the universe

00:23:53.170 --> 00:23:57.220
and the creator whose work
we celebrate on the Sabbath.

00:23:57.220 --> 00:24:00.170
There's so much to share here
about the beauty of the Sabbath

00:24:00.170 --> 00:24:03.520
and the fusion of the
spiritual with the scientific,

00:24:03.520 --> 00:24:05.530
and there are many
themes in this book

00:24:05.530 --> 00:24:08.850
that I haven't even
begun to deal with today.

00:24:08.850 --> 00:24:12.890
But let me show you just two more
pairs of paintings that relate

00:24:12.890 --> 00:24:14.770
to one of the most popular ways

00:24:14.770 --> 00:24:18.480
that we experience the material
world as the Sabbath arrives.

00:24:18.480 --> 00:24:24.710
Food. Challah, the special
braided egg bread that we eat

00:24:24.710 --> 00:24:28.210
on the Sabbath, is not
only the first thing eaten

00:24:28.210 --> 00:24:32.190
at the Sabbath dinner, but the
bread symbolizes all the bounty

00:24:32.190 --> 00:24:33.490
of the feast.

00:24:33.490 --> 00:24:35.910
And the act of baking
it most weeks is part

00:24:35.910 --> 00:24:39.210
of my own spiritual
preparation for the Sabbath.

00:24:39.210 --> 00:24:42.940
At right, I'm showing you
a meditation and painting

00:24:42.940 --> 00:24:45.820
about the act of kneading
the challah dough.

00:24:45.820 --> 00:24:50.000
And you can see in the bottom
left corner, right here,

00:24:50.000 --> 00:24:53.720
a little blob of dividing
yeast cells,

00:24:53.720 --> 00:24:57.720
that bit of microbiology
that defines bread.

00:24:57.720 --> 00:25:00.690
Above and below the painting,
you'll see a little meditation

00:25:00.690 --> 00:25:04.070
about the spiritual significance
of kneading the dough.

00:25:04.070 --> 00:25:06.940
This was a remarkable find for
me since these are the words

00:25:06.940 --> 00:25:10.300
of my ancestress pearl, the wife
of Rabbi [foreign language].

00:25:10.300 --> 00:25:17.000
At left, the blessing itself
surrounds an image expressing the

00:25:17.000 --> 00:25:21.080
mystical significance of the
act of breaking the bread.

00:25:21.080 --> 00:25:25.390 position:56%
The shadowy winged figures represent
the seraphim, who, as you'll read

00:25:25.390 --> 00:25:28.530
in the book, mystic
suggested to him the feast.

00:25:28.530 --> 00:25:34.080
The two loaves are set within a
view of the deep cosmos, again,

00:25:34.080 --> 00:25:38.260
that Hubble photograph, suggesting
the all suffusing divine,

00:25:38.260 --> 00:25:42.900
and the hills of Judah
burgeoning with the wheat harvest.

00:25:42.900 --> 00:25:45.790
And after the meal,
after singing some songs,

00:25:45.790 --> 00:25:49.030
all of which are also
here, we thank the almighty

00:25:49.030 --> 00:25:51.140
for the bounty of creation.

00:25:51.140 --> 00:25:56.320
Jewish tradition precedes the
grace after meals with Psalm 126,

00:25:56.320 --> 00:25:58.690
that we describe as Shir Ha'maalot.

00:25:58.690 --> 00:26:02.080
And these paintings tie
the miracle of the rebirth

00:26:02.080 --> 00:26:06.800
of the Jewish homeland, about
which the psalm remembers dreaming,

00:26:06.800 --> 00:26:11.250 position:56%
to the biological and
agricultural wonder of bringing food

00:26:11.250 --> 00:26:14.010
from our sacred soil once again.

00:26:14.010 --> 00:26:16.340
There's some wonderful
archaeology here.

00:26:16.340 --> 00:26:19.470
Imagery from Orr [phonetic],
Abraham's home,

00:26:19.470 --> 00:26:23.790
from the first Temple Period and
from the early Byzantine Period.

00:26:23.790 --> 00:26:28.020
But I want to draw your attention
to the two agricultural paintings.

00:26:28.020 --> 00:26:32.170
At right, the semicircular
painting shows a woman,

00:26:32.170 --> 00:26:36.400
the mourning woman Jerusalem
of Jeremiah, traipsing away

00:26:36.400 --> 00:26:40.850
from her destroyed home,
dragging a bag of seed.

00:26:40.850 --> 00:26:44.810
What she can't see happening
behind her is that water,

00:26:44.810 --> 00:26:48.300
a symbol of wisdom and torah
throughout our sources,

00:26:48.300 --> 00:26:52.370
is starting to flow again, and
those seeds falling from her bag,

00:26:52.370 --> 00:26:54.840
they're actually beginning
to germinate.

00:26:54.840 --> 00:26:59.940
Above her, the deep sky reminds
us of the all suffusing presence

00:26:59.940 --> 00:27:04.110
of the divine, of the unity
of the entire physical world.

00:27:04.110 --> 00:27:09.300
At left, we flash forward to the
miracle of the modern rebirth

00:27:09.300 --> 00:27:12.830
of the land and the
advent of modern Israel.

00:27:12.830 --> 00:27:14.600
The locale incidentally in both

00:27:14.600 --> 00:27:19.540
of these paintings is a
spot on [foreign language].

00:27:19.540 --> 00:27:23.740
Now, the dream of the
resettlement of Israel is reality.

00:27:23.740 --> 00:27:28.030
And again we draw sustenance
from the land.

00:27:28.030 --> 00:27:32.270
The fields and hills sprout with
date palms, crops, and vines.

00:27:32.270 --> 00:27:35.450
And farm workers use
tractors to harvest the bounty

00:27:35.450 --> 00:27:39.800
for which we give thanks
as we end the evening.

00:27:39.800 --> 00:27:43.450
I hope that these paintings

00:27:43.450 --> 00:27:48.050
at your table will spur discussion
among both adults and children

00:27:48.050 --> 00:27:51.140
about what it means to
celebrate the Sabbath.

00:27:51.140 --> 00:27:56.110
I've developed a small paperback
bench or table side condition

00:27:56.110 --> 00:27:59.320
of the home and table
materials, so that all can share

00:27:59.320 --> 00:28:02.200 position:56%
